            <abstract><p>Fears invasion by French but concedes that Bonaparte "will have been so far a benefactor to Englishmen that he will have taught us the value of the blessings Providence allows us". A 'Myrtus', the only one to grow between three attempted by her and Lady [Sophia] de Clifford, has flowered. A 'Cobben' Smith gave her the seeds, a creeper with purple flowers, has been grown by [Amelia] Long [ne√© Hume (1762-1837) daughter of Amelia and Abraham Hume, watercolour painter], has asked her to draw it.</p></abstract>
